text: Bjørg Holmsen, née Gulvik (13 June 1931 – 4 January 2015) is a Norwegian politician for the Conservative Party. She served as a deputy representative to the Parliament of Norway from Vestfold during the term 1973-1977\. In total she met during 7 days of parliamentary session. She was also mayor of Brunlanes from 1976 to 1987.Bjørg Holmsen ==References== Category:1931 births Category:2015 deaths Category:People from Larvik Category:Deputy members of the Storting Category:Conservative Party (Norway) politicians Category:Mayors of places in Vestfold Category:Women members of the Storting Category:Women mayors of places in Norway
